arr1 = [
    "The admission process for Gautam Buddha University (GBU) involves registering for and appearing in the university's entrance exam, the GBU-ET, though some flagship programs accept national-level exam scores like JEE Main, GATE, or CLAT. For other courses, admissions may be based on merit in the last qualifying exam, and the final admission step for all programs is the counseling and document verification process.",
    "Step 1 of admission process: Online Registration — Candidates must register on the GBU admission portal by providing their email, phone number, personal and academic details, and uploading required documents.",
    "Step 2 of admission process: Application Fee — Applicants must pay the online application fee.",
    "Step 3 of admission process: Submit Form — Submit the completed application form and keep the application number for future reference.",
    "Step 4 of admission process: Entrance Exam or Selection — Most programs require appearing for the GBU Entrance Test (GBU-ET). Some programs like B.Tech and MBA also accept scores from national-level exams such as JEE Main, GATE, CLAT, or CAT. For certain other programs, admissions are based purely on merit in the previous qualifying examination.",
    "Step 5 of admission process: Counseling and Document Verification — Candidates must attend the counseling session in person with both original and photocopied documents for verification and to complete admission formalities.",
    "Step 6 of admission process: Fee Payment — The required admission fee must be paid during the counseling session to confirm the seat.",
    "GBU use to conduct its own entrance exam, the GBU-ET, which is used for shortlisting candidates for most courses but they do not anymore.",
    "For certain programs, scores from national-level exams like JEE Main, GATE, CLAT, or CAT are accepted",
    "Some programs allow direct admission purely on the basis of merit in the qualifying exam, without requiring any entrance test.",
    "Counseling is the final stage of the admission process. Students must attend in person with all required documents and be ready to pay the admission fee to secure their seat.",
    "Candidates should ensure they meet the minimum eligibility criteria for the program they are applying for before beginning the admission process."
]

